-- Egyptian Stocks: Orascom Construction and Orascom Development
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-01-10T10:20:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/egyptian-stocks-orascom-construction-and-orascom-development.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index 
increased 1 percent to 3,686.53 at 11:49 a.m. in Cairo, heading
for the highest close in almost three weeks.  The following were among active equities on the Egyptian
Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC)   gained 1.7
percent to 207 pounds, the highest intraday level in a week.
Egypt’s biggest publicly traded builder said its partnership
with  Belgium ’s Besix Group will sign a contract with the
Egyptian government today to build the country’s planned Grand
Egyptian Museum.  Orascom Development Holding AG (ODHN)   advanced as much
as 1.8 percent before trading 0.2 percent higher at 4.38
Egyptian pounds. The Altdorf, Switzerland-based resorts
developer said Ali El Hitamy, the current head of international
construction, will assume responsibility for the company’s
Egyptian operations on June 1 after vice chairman and co-chief
executive officer Amr Sheta leaves its management team on May 7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
